{
  "texts": [
    "However, it can be observed that the model trained only for T 2 lags behind T5-base_CL in terms of CRR1 F 1 and P LOW T 1 (x) both.",
    "QueryShield contains all three models, i.e., Attn-BERT, T5-base_CL, and Mistral-7B-Instruct_CL, configured by the system administrator considering -(i) accuracy, (ii) inference time per query (Mistral-7B-Instruct_CL: 1.4 sec vs T5-base_CL: 0.3 sec), (iii) and fine-tuning capability where a model can be fine-tuned using incremental training data from user feedback.",
    "Default recommendations for the best end-to-end accuracy would be using T5-base_CL for T 1, Mistral-7B-Instruct_CL for T 2 and Attn-BERT for T 3.",
    "Long queries: One advantage that Mistral has over T5 is its longer context window.",
    "Hence, for a query longer than 512 tokens, Mistral model is preferred for rephrasing."
  ]
}